moves.1. e4 e5 2. f4 Nc6 3. Nc3 exf4 4. Nf3 d6: To here, fairly standard lines for a Vienna gambit game.
moves.10. Re1 O-O-O 11. Bb2 Bd7: Brings pressure to the King-side, but removes any threat to the KP.
moves.12... g4: The knight is unguarded, with no retreat square - but this loses the game or the Queen.
moves.13. Nd5 Qf8: Possibly the worst option, as the Queen is un-developed.  But the game is gone anyway.  Necessary was b6 or Bc6.
moves.14. Qa5: Black has nothing left but garbage moves: mate on either c7 or a8 within 3.
moves.14... b6 15. Qxa7 Bxd4+ 16. Bxd4 gxf3: Well, he did take the knight.
